<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-017-089 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 511 058</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Nov 4 1991 n666 p10(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Komag grabs Dastek to enter thin-film heads. (leading independentdisk drive media vendor will be able to supply both heads andmedia)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Costlow, Terry.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Leading independent disk drive media vendor Komag Inc will buythin-film head maker Dastek Inc for three million shares of Komagstock.andP;  The acquisition will make Komag the first independentvendor to market both media and thin-film heads.andP;  Komag previouslyacquired thin-film head technology from Siemens, but thatoperation will not ramp up until mid-1992.andP;  The Dastek purchasewill provide Komag with production capability immediately if thedeal is completed.andP;  The acquisition will also make Komag one ofthe four major thin-film manufacturers in a market that isexpected to double in 1991 and grow about 30 percent in both 1992and 1993.andP;  There are advantages in manufacturing both media andheads, but Komag will not force customers to buy both from theKomag/Dastek operations.andP;  Dastek is the fourth-largest thin-filmhead maker with 18 percent of the market compared to market-leaderRead-Rite's 39 percent.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Komag Inc. (Acquisitions, mergers, divestments)Dastek Corp. (Acquisitions, mergers, divestments).andO;Ticker:    KMAG.andO;Topic:     Thin-Film RecordingRead/Write HeadsMagnetic MediaManufacturersAcquisitionImpact AnalysisCompetition.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>